```
In this example, we have two default cases, but only one of them will execute. The first default case with the keyword "default" will run if no other case matches.

An example of using a case statement with a single statement in Actian 4GL OpenROAD is:
```
case lowercase(inputselection) of
     default : value = 0;
     'one'   : value = 1;
     'two'   : value = 2;
     'three' : value = 3;
endcase;
```
This type of construct is the equivalent of an array lookup using a string value as the index.
